'''Mário Ricardo da Silva Velho''' (born 20 August 1998) is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Liga Portugal 2]] club [[S.C. Farense|Farense]], and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]].

==Club career==
===Braga===
Born in [[Vila Nova de Famalicão]], [[Braga District]], Velho joined [[S.C. Braga|Braga]]'s academy when he was 14.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mundodosguardaredes.pt/ricardo-velho-16-anos-promovido-ao-sc/|title=Ricardo Velho (16 anos) promovido ao SC Braga B|trans-title=Ricardo Velho (aged 16) promoted to SC Braga B|publisher=Mundo dos Guarda-Redes|first=Roberto|last=Rivelino|language=pt|date=3 July 2015|access-date=7 November 2023}}</ref> On 23 August 2017, he made his professional debut with the [[S.C. Braga B|reserve team]] in a 2–1 away loss against [[F.C. Penafiel|Penafiel]] in the [[Liga Portugal 2|LigaPro]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/penafiel-sp-braga-b-2-1-durienses-ficam-com-os-tres-pontos|title=Penafiel-Sp. Braga B, 2–1: Durienses ficam com os três pontos|trans-title=Penafiel-Sp. Braga B, 2–1: ''Durienses'' take the three points|newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|language=pt|date=23 August 2017|access-date=7 November 2023}}</ref>

During his spell, Velho played second-fiddle to [[Tiago Sá]] (who later appeared in several matches for the main squad) and Rogério Santos.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/i/10717343.html/|title=Há um outro Tiago a nascer na baliza do Braga e pode ocupar a vaga de Marafona|trans-title=Another Tiago is being born in Braga's goal and he may take Marafona's place|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|first=Pedro|last=Rocha|language=pt|date=23 March 2019|access-date=7 November 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/bola-branca/noticia/futebol-nacional/2020/01/15/braga-renova-com-jovem-guarda-redes-da-equipa-b/178528/|title=Braga renova com jovem guarda-redes da equipa B|trans-title=Braga renew with young B-team goalkeeper|publisher=[[Rádio Renascença]]|language=pt|date=15 January 2020|access-date=7 November 2023}}</ref>

===Farense===
On 31 July 2020, Velho signed a two-year contract with [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.C. Farense|Farense]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/farense/detalhe/ricardo-velho-e-reforco-para-a-baliza-do-farense|title=Ricardo Velho é reforço para a baliza do Farense|trans-title=Ricardo Velho is addition for Farense goal|newspaper=Record|first=Armando|last=Alves|language=pt|date=31 July 2020|access-date=7 November 2023}}</ref> In the [[2022–23 Liga Portugal 2|2022–23 season]], he contributed 22 games as his side finished runners-up and returned to the main division after a two-year absence, while they conceded a league-best 34 goals; subsequently, he agreed to an extension until June 2026.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/farense/noticias/ricardo-velho-renova-com-o-farense-ate-2026-16735519.html/|title=Ricardo Velho renova com o Farense até 2026|trans-title=Ricardo Velho renews with Farense until 2026|newspaper=O Jogo|language=pt|date=22 July 2023|access-date=7 November 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/velho-ate-2025-2023081016580522388|title=Farense Velho até {{sic|nolink=y|2025}}|trans-title=Farense Velho until 2026|newspaper=[[A Bola]]|language=pt|date=22 July 2023|access-date=7 November 2023}}</ref>

Velho's maiden appearance in the top flight took place on 12 August 2023, in a 0–3 home defeat to [[Casa Pia A.C.|Casa Pia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.avozdoalgarve.pt/d/casa-pia-vence-farense-na-estreia-na-i-liga-2023-24/72405|title=Casa Pia vence Farense na estreia na I Liga 2023/24|trans-title=Casa Pia beat Farense in 2023/24 I League opener|newspaper=A Voz do Algarve|language=pt|date=12 August 2023|access-date=7 November 2023}}</ref> Due to his performances, which included a league-best 143 saves and seven [[Shutout#Association football|clean sheets]] with Farense finishing tenth, he was voted [[2023–24 Primeira Liga|the campaign]]'s Goalkeeper of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cnnportugal.iol.pt/liga/ricardo-velho/ricardo-velho-eleito-o-guarda-redes-da-epoca-2023-24-na-liga|title=Ricardo Velho eleito o guarda-redes da época 2023/24 na Liga|trans-title=Ricardo Velho voted goalkeeper of the 2023/24 season in League|publisher=[[CNN Portugal]]|language=pt|date=3 June 2024|access-date=7 November 2024}}</ref><ref name=GOTY>{{cite news|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/farense-ricardo-velho-eleito-guarda-redes-do-ano-2024060319145848649|title=Farense: Ricardo Velho eleito guarda-redes do ano|trans-title=Farense: Ricardo Velho voted goalkeeper of the year|newspaper=A Bola|first=Jorge|last=Anjinho|language=pt|date=3 June 2024|access-date=14 June 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/bola-branca/especial/futebol-nacional/2024/10/03/de-que-e-que-estamos-a-espera-a-candidatura-de-ricardo-velho-a-selecao-por-tres-pessoas-que-o-conhecem-bem/395827/|title="De que é que estamos à espera?" A candidatura de Ricardo Velho à seleção, por três pessoas que o conhecem bem|trans-title="What are we waiting for?" Ricardo Velho's candidacy to the national team, by three people who know him well|publisher=Rádio Renascença|first=Inês|last=Braga Sampaio|language=pt|date=3 October 2024|access-date=7 November 2024}}</ref>

In summer 2024, Velho was linked with a move to [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], but the deal fell through when Farense demanded that his €10 million [[buyout clause]] be paid. This led to him agreeing to extend his contract until 2028.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jn.pt/2423153671/ricardo-velho-renova-com-farense-ate-2028/|title=Ricardo Velho renova com Farense até 2028|trans-title=Ricardo Velho renews with Farense until 2028|newspaper=[[Jornal de Notícias]]|language=pt|date=20 September 2024|access-date=4 November 2024}}</ref>

Velho missed the final month of [[2024–25 Primeira Liga|2024–25]], due to a knee ligament injury that required surgery.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/farense-terminou-a-epoca-para-ricardo-velho-2025042916423902382?srsltid=AfmBOooCtSGvl-08Bk0-4j88Q7DG59D6NsqPjlTBxol8uAXHGF9u22hr|title=Farense: terminou a época para Ricardo Velho|trans-title=Farense: season over for Ricardo Velho|newspaper=A Bola|first=Jorge|last=Anjinho|language=pt|date=29 April 2025|access-date=16 July 2025}}</ref> His team would be ultimately relegated as second-bottom.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/1a-liga/toze-marreco-deixa-comando-tecnico-do-farense-por-mutuo-acordo_d1658529|title=Tozé Marreco deixa o Farense|trans-title=Tozé Marreco leaves Farense|publisher=[[Rádio e Televisão de Portugal]]|language=pt|date=29 May 2025|access-date=16 July 2025}}</ref>

Shortly after the start of the [[2025–26 Süper Lig|following season]], Velho was loaned to [[Gençlerbirliği S.K.|Gençlerbirliği]] with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abola.pt/noticias/oficial-ricardo-velho-troca-o-farense-pela-turquia-2025091222011331797|title=Oficial: Ricardo Velho troca o Farense pela Turquia|trans-title=Official: Ricardo Velho swaps Farense for Turkey|newspaper=A Bola|first=David|last=Nunes|language=pt|date=12 September 2025|access-date=13 September 2025}}</ref> He only made his [[Süper Lig]] debut on 7 November, in a 2–1 home win over [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]]; manager [[Volkan Demirel]] later disclosed that he was fielded because the Turkish club would have to pay €200.000 in compensation if he did not take part in the required number of matches in the first half of the campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/made-in/turquia/turquia-velho-estreia-se-pelo-genclerbirligi-por-motivos-contratuais|title=Turquia: Velho estreia-se pelo Gençlerbirligi por motivos contratuais|trans-title=Turkey: Velho makes Gençlerbirligi debut for contractual reasons|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=pt|date=8 November 2025|access-date=11 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sapo.pt/artigo/quase-tres-meses-sem-jogar-e-uma-clausula-levou-o-a-estreia-ricardo-velho-e-tema-na-turquia-69122cdf5867210093ee786c|title=Quase três meses sem jogar e uma cláusula levou-o à estreia: Ricardo Velho é tema na Turquia|trans-title=Almost three months without playing and a clause led to his debut: Ricardo Velho the talk of the town in Turkey|publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]]|language=pt|date=10 November 2025|access-date=11 November 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Velho was not [[Cap (sport)|capped]] by Portugal at any [[Portugal national youth football team|youth level]]. On 4 October 2024, he was called by the [[Portugal national football team|senior team]] for matches against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] and [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/selecao-nacional/ricardo-velho-e-samu-costa-chamados-por-martinez_d1604827|title=Ricardo Velho e Samú Costa chamados por Martínez|trans-title=Ricardo Velho and Samú Costa called by Martínez|publisher=Rádio e Televisão de Portugal|first=Mário|last=Aleixo|language=pt|date=4 October 2024|access-date=5 October 2024}}</ref>

On 31 March 2026, Velho made his full debut, coming on as an 85th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[José Sá]] in a 2–0 [[Exhibition game#International football|friendly]] victory over the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] in [[Atlanta]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/762259|title=Portugal outclasses U.S. amid Christian Pulisic goal drought|publisher=[[ESPN]]|date=1 April 2026|access-date=1 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/internacional/artigo/ricardo-velho-e-mateus-fernandes-elevam-para-16-os-estreantes-na-era-roberto-martinez/18068429|title=Ricardo Velho e Mateus Fernandes elevam para 16 os estreantes na 'era' Roberto Martínez|trans-title=Ricardo Velho and Mateus Fernandes make it 16 debutants in the Roberto Martínez 'era'|newspaper=O Jogo|language=pt|date=1 April 2026|access-date=1 April 2026}}</ref> He was selected for [[2026 FIFA World Cup|the year]]'s [[FIFA World Cup]] as an emergency-only fourth goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/2026/05/19/the-reason-portugal-called-up-4-goalkeepers-for-world-cup-reason-to-fret-for-cristiano-ronaldo-fans.html|title=The reason Portugal called up 4 goalkeepers for World Cup: No reason to fret for Cristiano Ronaldo fans|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|first=Matias|last=Wodner|date=19 May 2026|access-date=1 June 2026}}</ref>

